verses.roman:
rāghava-paṇḍita cale jhāli sājāiyā
damayantī yata dravya diyāche kariyā

synonyms: rāghava-paṇḍita—Rāghava Paṇḍita; cale—goes; jhāli sājāiyā—after preparing his bag of food; damayantī—his sister; yata dravya—all the goods; diyāche kariyā—cooked and prepared.
translation: Rāghava Paṇḍita came with bags full of food prepared very nicely by his sister, Damayantī.
